{"word":"χαλκεύω","slug":"χαλκεύω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>χαλκεύω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:χαλκός'><el>χαλκός</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to make of copper</i> or (generally) <i>of metal, to forge</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>:—<a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a> <i>to forge for oneself</i>, <b><a href='S:Theognis'>Theogn.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to be wrought</i> or <i>forged</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a> <i>to be a smith, work as a smith, ply the hammer</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b>; <el>τὸ χαλκεύειν</el> <i>the smith's art</i>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}